{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:08.053Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF) refines a model using "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "human preference signals",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " so outputs better match what people want—helpfulness, harmlessness, honesty. For agents, alignment reduces unsafe tool calls, toxic replies, and policy violations while preserving task competence."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Classic RLHF pipeline:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "attrs": {
          "start": 1,
          "type": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Supervised fine-tuning on demonstrations"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Train a reward model on human comparisons (A better than B)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Optimize policy with PPO (or similar) to maximize reward while staying close to the SFT model via KL penalty"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Objective sketch: maximize "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\mathbb{E}[R(x,y)] - \\beta \\, \\mathrm{KL}(\\pi_\\theta \\| \\pi_{\\text{ref}})"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " where "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "R"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is reward model score, "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\beta"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " controls deviation from reference."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Instruction tuning alone does not encode nuanced preferences—how cautious to be with destructive tools, how to refuse jailbreaks, or how verbose to be. RLHF encodes these trade-offs from human raters. Agent vendors apply similar stages before releasing models with function-calling APIs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Alternatives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "DPO",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — direct preference optimization without explicit reward model; common in open models"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RLAIF",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — AI feedback instead of humans for scale"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Constitutional AI",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — model critiques and revises outputs against principles"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Expensive human labeling; bias in rater pool"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reward hacking—model optimizes superficial cues"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Over-alignment can reduce creativity or refusal of benign edge cases"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "PPO training instability; DPO simpler but has its own failure modes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agentic AI connection"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Aligned models refuse disallowed tool use more reliably and follow system policies in multi-turn attacks. Alignment does not replace runtime guards—tool allowlists, sandboxing, and output validation remain mandatory. RLHF-shaped models are the reason \"helpful assistant\" behavior exists out of the box."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Security and reliability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Combine alignment with red-teaming for prompt injection and tool abuse"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Monitor reward drift when fine-tuning aligned models further"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Document KL/reference model when continuing training"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RLHF: SFT → reward model → RL with KL to reference"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Encodes preferences instruction tuning misses"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "DPO/RLAIF are widely used modern variants"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agents still need runtime controls beyond alignment"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
